oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Mr. Clement measures a black walnut
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Owens, R.H., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: W.L. Clement scales twenty seven inches of black walnut tree of veneer quality that will bring between one hundred and one hundred twenty-five dollars per hundred board foot.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
